nc_cat=110&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=6e7a0a&_nc_ohc=8ao1SUmlRpMQ7kNvgFrZFnc&_nc_ht=scontent.oculuscdn.com&_nc_gid=ACH0xMA9TCeT_pmSHXP56wT&oh=00_AYA9Z5j67WHPtck-84QK520JhxpmYs5Yi9NuYNpVKww-1A&oe=66EA9DBC"}, "display_name": "3D scan of a semi-medieval town", "keywords": [], "long_description": "Move like a pedestrian in a semi-medieval town, reconstructed from videos taken by a helmet-held 360 camera, whose trajectory is about 1km long.\n\nRight controller:\n- Rotate on the left or right by using the joystick\n- Update the vertical offset (up or down) by using the joystick\n- Choose a location and teleport to it by using the virtual laser pointer\n- Teleport by using the index trigger only if the laser is green (not red)\n\nLeft controller:\n- Move continuously by using the joystick\n- Switch pannel and map by using the grip/hand trigger\n- If both map and pannel are disabled, switch between rendering modes (texturing or normal colors) by pressing the index trigger\n- The map shows the cloud of mesh vertices and the user location\n- If the pannel is enabled, switch between constrained and unconstrained motions by pressing the index trigger\n- The constrained motion controls your height above the ground\n- The pannel shows information about the 3D model and the selected motion.\n", "short_description": "Move continuously like a pedestrian in a semi-medieval town, which was computed by photogrammetry from a cubemap video (4096x1344x2) taken by a helmet-held 360 camera (Gopro Max) and by walking about 1km in a town (Montpeyroux, in France)."}]}, "developer_name": "Maxime Lhuillier", "developer_privacy_policy_url": "https://maximelhuillier.fr/", "developer_terms_of_service_url": null, "publisher_name": "Unity 2019.4", "support_website_url": "http://maxime.lhuillier.free.fr/", "website_url": "https://maximelhuillier.fr/", "category": "ENTERTAINMENT", "comfort_rating": "NOT_RATED", "comfort_tags": [], "context_category": null, "context_topics": [], "external_subscription_type": "NOT_